## 3. JSON‑LD must render in SSR HTML

- Compute structured data (JSON‑LD) in `+page.server.ts` (`schemaData`) and return it.
- Render with **`JsonLdHead`** (`$lib/ui/components/seo/JsonLdHead.svelte`) so crawlers receive real JSON (Svelte does not interpolate inside `<script type="application/ld+json">` tags):

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import JsonLdHead from '$lib/ui/components/seo/JsonLdHead.svelte';
  let schemaData = $derived(data.schemaData);
</script>

<JsonLdHead schemaData={schemaData} />
```

Serialization helper: `$lib/utils/jsonLdScriptHtml.ts` (`serializeJsonLd`, `jsonLdScriptHtml`). Docs pages use the same helper in `DocsSeoHead.svelte`.

Avoid:
- `<script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify(schemaData)}</script>` — renders the literal string in SSR HTML.
- Generating JSON‑LD only in `onMount` (not SSR-visible).
- Putting JSON‑LD behind client-only conditions (`if (browser)`).
- Inline `schemaData={{ '@context': … }}` objects in `+page.svelte`.
- Hardcoding `'@context': 'https://schema.org'` in routes — use the shared helpers below.

### Typed JSON-LD (`schema-dts` + `jsonLdSchema`)

All JSON-LD in this codebase is typed with [`schema-dts`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/schema-dts) and built through **`$lib/utils/jsonLdSchema.ts`**:

| Export | Use |
| --- | --- |
| `SCHEMA_ORG_CONTEXT` | Canonical `@context` value (`https://schema.org`) |
| `JsonLdGraphSchema` | Return type for multi-node `@graph` documents |
| `JsonLdGraphNode` | A single node inside `@graph` (`Thing`) |
| `createJsonLdGraph(nodes)` | Build `{ '@context', '@graph': [...] }` |
| `createJsonLdWithContext(node)` | Build a single top-level node with `@context` (no `@graph`) |
| `filterNonEmptyJsonLdNodes(nodes)` | Drop optional helpers that return `{}` when empty |

Import `schema-dts` types for individual nodes (`WebPage`, `CollectionPage`, `WebApplication`, `FAQPage`, `Person`, `HowTo`, etc.) and annotate graph nodes with `satisfies` where it helps catch typos.

**`@graph` (most pages):**

```ts
import type { WebSite } from 'schema-dts';

import { createPublicFaqSEOSchema } from '$lib/content/utils/createPublicFaqSEOSchema';
import { createJsonLdGraph, filterNonEmptyJsonLdNodes } from '$lib/utils/jsonLdSchema';

const canonical = new URL(url.pathname, url.origin).href;

const schemaData = createJsonLdGraph(
  filterNonEmptyJsonLdNodes([
    {
      '@type': 'WebSite',
      '@id': `${url.origin}/#website`,
      name: companyName,
      url: url.origin,
      description: heroDescription
    },
    createPublicFaqSEOSchema({
      pageUrl: `${canonical}#faq`,
      name: faqTitle,
      description: faqDescription,
      items: faqItems
    })
  ])
);
```

**Single-node (rare — e.g. `/tools/skill-builder` index):**

```ts
import type { WebApplication } from 'schema-dts';

import { createJsonLdWithContext } from '$lib/utils/jsonLdSchema';

const schemaData = createJsonLdWithContext({
  '@type': 'WebApplication',
  name: metaTitle,
  description: metaDescription,
  applicationCategory: 'DeveloperApplication',
  offers: { '@type': 'Offer', price: '0', priceCurrency: 'USD' }
} satisfies WebApplication);
```

### Reusable schema builders

When JSON-LD logic is non-trivial or reused, put it in `$lib/<domain>/utils/` and call it from `+page.server.ts` — not from `+page.svelte`. Builders return typed `schema-dts` nodes or `JsonLdGraphSchema`:

| Helper | Path | Returns |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `createPublicFaqSEOSchema` | `$lib/content/utils/createPublicFaqSEOSchema.ts` | `FAQPage` or `{}` |
| `createLandingDemoSEOSchema` | `$lib/content/utils/createLandingDemoSEOSchema.ts` | `VideoObject` or `{}` |
| `createOrganizationSEOSchema` | `$lib/content/utils/createOrganizationSEOSchema.ts` | `Organization` |
| `createBlogPostSEOSchema` | `$lib/blogs/utils/createBlogPostSEOSchema.ts` | `JsonLdGraphSchema` |
| `createPostSEOSchema` | `$lib/posts/utils/createPostSEOSchema.ts` | `JsonLdGraphSchema` |
| `createListingSEOSchema` | `$lib/listings/utils/listingSchema.ts` | `JsonLdGraphSchema` |
| `mergeListingSchemaIntoGraph` | `$lib/listings/utils/listingSchema.ts` | `Thing[]` — merges CMS `schemaJson` into a base graph |
| `createCollectionPageSchema`, `create*ItemListSchema`, `create*TermSetSchema` | `$lib/listings/utils/createPlaybooksSeoSchema.ts` | playbooks hub / category / tag pages |
| Same pattern for building blocks | `$lib/listings/utils/createBuildingBlocksSeoSchema.ts` | building-blocks hub / category / tag pages |

Hub server loads (`loadPlaybooksHubPage.server.ts`, `loadBuildingBlocksHubPage.server.ts`) compose these builders with `createJsonLdGraph` + `filterNonEmptyJsonLdNodes`.

### Reference graph shapes by route type

| Route type | Typical `@graph` nodes |
| --- | --- |
| **Landing** | `WebSite` + `Organization` + `FAQPage` + `VideoObject` |
| **About** | `AboutPage` + `Organization` |
| **Pricing** | `WebPage` (with `Offer` list) + `FAQPage` |
| **Hub** (`/channels`, `/agents`, `/tools`, …) | `CollectionPage` + `ItemList` (+ optional `FAQPage`) |
| **Channel / agent detail** | `WebPage` + `SoftwareApplication` + `FAQPage` |
| **Tool pages** | `WebApplication` (+ `WebSite` `isPartOf` on channel routes) |
| **Blog / post preview** | `BlogPosting` or `SocialMediaPosting` + `BreadcrumbList` (+ `Comment` nodes) |
| **Creator profile** | `ProfilePage` + `Person` |
| **Playbook detail** | `WebPage` + `Person` + `HowTo` or `CreativeWork` |
| **Building block detail** | `WebPage` + `Person` + merged listing `schemaJson` |
| **Compare** | `WebPage` + `ItemList` + `SoftwareApplication` × 2 + `FAQPage` |

Do not duplicate title/description strings for JSON-LD in the component when they already exist in the server load.

### FAQPage (`createPublicFaqSEOSchema`)

- Builds `FAQPage` with `mainEntity` → `Question` / `acceptedAnswer` → `Answer` (`text` must be plain text, matching visible accordion copy).
- Pass `pageUrl: `${canonical}#faq`` and the **same** section `name` / `description` shown in `PublicFaq`.
- Returns `{}` when `items` is empty — always pass through `filterNonEmptyJsonLdNodes` when composing a `@graph`.
- Default `items` is `PUBLIC_FAQ_ITEMS`; only override when a route renders a different FAQ list.

### VideoObject (`createLandingDemoSEOSchema`)

- Builds `VideoObject` for the landing demo (`DEMO_YOUTUBE_VIDEO_ID`, `DEMO_TITLE`, `DEMO_DESCRIPTION` from SSR `landing_page` config).
- Include in landing `@graph` alongside `WebSite`, `Organization`, and `FAQPage`.
- Returns `{}` when `youtubeVideoId` is empty — filter before emitting.
- `HeroDemo` must expose crawlable demo URLs in SSR HTML: thumbnail `<img alt="…">`, `ExternalLink` to `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={id}`, and section `id="landing-demo"`.

### Organization (`createOrganizationSEOSchema`)

- Emit on **landing** and **about** — not sitewide on every layout.
- Use `organizationSchemaId(origin)` for stable `@id` cross-linking (`{origin}/#organization`).
- `sameAs` defaults to marketing social URLs via `resolveSocialSameAsUrls()`.

